1
00:00:13,320 --> 00:00:17,223
Live for long, and I only end up
sleeping in somebody's garage...

2
00:00:17,223 --> 00:00:18,826
Look what our life is...

3
00:00:18,826 --> 00:00:22,730
You said it... This is like a horse-stable
of a house in the old days.

4
00:00:22,830 --> 00:00:25,633
Mom, thanks to you we really
gain worldly experience.

5
00:00:25,733 --> 00:00:28,736
Ms. Gil Seon Ja, you're the best.

6
00:00:28,736 --> 00:00:31,238
Whatever you say, I am your mom,
so what can you do about it?

7
00:00:31,338 --> 00:00:32,740
Just take it as your fate.

8
00:00:32,740 --> 00:00:34,141
Who said anything here?

9
00:00:34,441 --> 00:00:36,944
How come it is so cold? 
You didn't turn on the hot mat?

10
00:00:36,944 --> 00:00:39,647
I did. The water in it isn't warm yet.

11
00:00:39,847 --> 00:00:43,550
See, had I not redeemed at least this hot mat,
you think we could've slept in such a place?

12
00:00:43,651 --> 00:00:45,352
It's the hot mats that made us
sleep in such a place.

13
00:00:45,352 --> 00:00:46,954
Your sense of reality is in the pits, really!

14
00:00:46,954 --> 00:00:48,355
In the pits? You wretched girl...

15
00:00:48,455 --> 00:00:49,956
It's cold.

16
00:00:50,057 --> 00:00:53,560
If you want so much to get away from me,
you leave.

17
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:54,962
I will stay like this temporarily.

18
00:00:54,962 --> 00:00:56,263
Temporarily until when?

19
00:00:56,263 --> 00:01:00,067
I won't tell you. Just know that living 
apart from you is the wish of my life.

20
00:01:00,167 --> 00:01:03,671
Attain your life's wish now itself.
Live apart. Hurry, leave now.

21
00:01:03,771 --> 00:01:05,773
You just wait. I will do just that.

22
00:01:05,773 --> 00:01:07,775
What? You let them stay in the garage?

23
00:01:07,775 --> 00:01:10,477
You out of your mind?
How can you let people stay in the garage?

24
00:01:10,477 --> 00:01:13,981
Even the garage won't work?
What you are doing is too much!

25
00:01:13,981 --> 00:01:15,683
Too much or too small,
get them out quickly.

26
00:01:15,683 --> 00:01:18,285
Min Hyeok is in that shape. Why the heck
bring outsiders into the house?

27
00:01:18,285 --> 00:01:19,887
Even families have secrets to keep.

28
00:01:19,987 --> 00:01:22,189
They have nowhere to go, you know.
They are Soe Dol's family.

29
00:01:22,189 --> 00:01:24,491
Soe Dol's family, so what?
How long back did he die?

30
00:01:24,491 --> 00:01:27,394
Absolutely no way.
Send them out first thing tomorrow morning!

31
00:01:27,394 --> 00:01:29,496
Damn, I'm cancer-stricken!

32
00:01:29,496 --> 00:01:31,699
Cancer-stricken, so what?
Stop this old cancer talk.

33
00:01:31,799 --> 00:01:33,300
He said it's in an early stage.
Why go overboard like this?

34
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:37,104
It's not overboard. I know this.
My mom was in the same shape too.

35
00:01:38,205 --> 00:01:39,707
I know it...

36
00:01:40,908 --> 00:01:45,312
My ending will be the same as Mom's.
No mistaking it.

37
00:01:46,213 --> 00:01:49,116
My sad premonitions never miss the mark.

38
00:01:49,116 --> 00:01:51,719
Yeah right, sad premonition!
It never fails to go wrong.

39
00:01:51,719 --> 00:01:52,919
What?

40
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:54,321
What do you mean what?

41
00:01:54,321 --> 00:01:57,224
Bo Yeong wasn't feeling well, but did that
premonition say that she was pregnant?

42
00:01:57,324 --> 00:02:00,027
Father-in-law had blood in his stool, and did
the premonition say it was hemorrhoids?

43
00:02:00,027 --> 00:02:01,028
What had it got correct?

44
00:02:01,028 --> 00:02:02,830
Why bring up old matters?

45
00:02:03,631 --> 00:02:06,834
Anyway from now on,
I'll do things I wish to do.

46
00:02:06,934 --> 00:02:09,737
To those who did favors to me,
I want to do good things, okay?

47
00:02:09,837 --> 00:02:12,039
Only then will I have no regrets
whatever happens to me.

48
00:02:12,039 --> 00:02:14,642
Doing good things or repaying favors
is all up to you.

49
00:02:14,742 --> 00:02:17,745
Those people in the garage
must be sent out pronto tomorrow!

50
00:02:17,745 --> 00:02:20,447
Give a bit of thought to me losing face, please!

51
00:02:20,748 --> 00:02:21,749
What's with you, really?

52
00:02:21,849 --> 00:02:23,951
It's a garage that I gave to
them who deserve a room!

53
00:02:23,951 --> 00:02:26,153
Even that I cannot do? Really?

54
00:02:26,153 --> 00:02:27,755
Just give them money for
them to go find a place.

55
00:02:27,855 --> 00:02:30,457
Whatever... Forget it.
I too don't give a damn.

56
00:02:30,557 --> 00:02:33,661
When I'm already cancer-stricken,
must you make me lose face too?

57
00:02:33,761 --> 00:02:36,063
If I said no way, it means no way!

58
00:02:36,363 --> 00:02:38,565
But how do we eat some food?

59
00:02:38,565 --> 00:02:40,067
What do we do for a bathroom?

60
00:02:40,067 --> 00:02:42,569
They'll have to let us use a bathroom.

61
00:02:42,569 --> 00:02:44,471
Would they ask us to eat with them?

62
00:02:44,471 --> 00:02:45,973
That would be the best.

63
00:02:46,073 --> 00:02:48,676
Not sure of a bathroom, but eating... well...

64
00:02:48,976 --> 00:02:52,079
Rich people would never want to
face people like us.

65
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:53,480
Is it so?

66
00:02:53,981 --> 00:02:56,784
Well, anyway we get a good look
at a rich family's house.

67
00:02:56,784 --> 00:02:59,286
Where we step out from here
is a proper garden.

68
00:02:59,286 --> 00:03:00,287
<i>Huh?</i>

69
00:03:00,287 --> 00:03:02,089
<i>Don't step into the garden?</i>

70
00:03:02,189 --> 00:03:05,793
I had to agree on that with my wife. I am sorry.

71
00:03:05,893 --> 00:03:10,998
But if we can't step into the garden,
how can we come in?

72
00:03:10,998 --> 00:03:14,602
Through the roll-up shutter 
garage entrance.

73
00:03:14,602 --> 00:03:19,006
My wife has become damn sensitive lately
since our oldest son got hurt, that's why.

74
00:03:19,006 --> 00:03:20,507
Please understand it for me.

75
00:03:20,608 --> 00:03:26,213
If it's through the shutters, that means we wait
for a car to return and only then get in?

76
00:03:26,213 --> 00:03:28,515
I will get a garage remote made for you.

77
00:03:28,616 --> 00:03:33,120
On this itself, my wife was asking
how we could open it for outsiders?

78
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:35,022
I insisted that I would open it.

79
00:03:35,022 --> 00:03:36,523
Thank you so much.

80
00:03:36,523 --> 00:03:39,827
Then, let me know if there is any discomfort.

81
00:03:39,827 --> 00:03:41,629
Then, excuse me...

82
00:03:44,732 --> 00:03:46,634
From now on, what's going to happen?

83
00:03:47,034 --> 00:03:49,737
I'm told the CEO's falling incident
will be investigated by the police.

84
00:03:49,737 --> 00:03:50,638
Really?

85
00:03:50,738 --> 00:03:51,739
Yes.

86
00:03:51,839 --> 00:03:55,943
Seeing them investigate, it appears not to be
a pure accident. Who would have done it?

87
00:03:55,943 --> 00:03:56,844
Not sure.

88
00:03:56,944 --> 00:04:00,748
And also, there is a rumor that
the CEO's condition isn't normal.

89
00:04:00,748 --> 00:04:01,949
Really?

90
00:04:02,548 --> 00:04:06,654
Team leader, you go every day to top staff
meetings, but you seem clueless on this.

91
00:04:06,654 --> 00:04:07,755
An outcast now?

92
00:04:07,855 --> 00:04:09,156
Me?

93
00:04:12,559 --> 00:04:14,061
<i>Adviser, sir.</i>

94
00:04:16,964 --> 00:04:18,766
<i>You weren't supposed to step into the garden.</i>

95
00:04:19,266 --> 00:04:20,668
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

96
00:04:21,568 --> 00:04:22,569
<i>What is it?</i>

97
00:04:22,569 --> 00:04:27,174
<i>Could I ask you if the CEO is doing all right?</i>

98
00:04:27,174 --> 00:04:28,576
<i>I was just worried.</i>

99
00:04:28,576 --> 00:04:31,779
<i>He's fine. If you're asked at the company,
just say he is fine.</i>

100
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:38,986
<i>I told Chauffeur Gim to keep it a secret that you
are living at my house, so nobody will ask you.</i>

101
00:04:38,986 --> 00:04:40,588
<i>But don't come out and say anything.</i>

102
00:04:52,900 --> 00:04:54,401
<i>Why are you eating alone?</i>

103
00:04:54,501 --> 00:04:55,102
<i>What?</i>

104
00:04:55,102 --> 00:05:00,207
<i>An open outcast or 
quietly isolated?</i>

105
00:05:08,015 --> 00:05:09,116
What's this?

106
00:05:14,421 --> 00:05:16,824
Don't do this to me today, okay?

107
00:05:24,331 --> 00:05:28,736
<i>For this graphics, it's enough
if you fill in your survey data.
Try typing it.</i>

108
00:05:30,537 --> 00:05:34,341
Where did you go and why won't 
you show up? Hongberg...

109
00:05:35,042 --> 00:05:37,044
Miss Jin A, you aren't coming to the dinner party?

110
00:05:37,745 --> 00:05:40,047
I'll try finishing this proposal
and then come over.

111
00:05:41,248 --> 00:05:43,050
Do it later. Come fast.

112
00:05:46,353 --> 00:05:50,157
But, team leader, I shouldn't
think of having drinks today.

113
00:05:50,257 --> 00:05:51,959
Is it okay if I don't drink?

114
00:06:01,969 --> 00:06:04,171
I thought you said you wouldn't drink...

115
00:06:04,271 --> 00:06:06,073
Miss Jin A, is something wrong?

116
00:06:06,173 --> 00:06:07,875
Or something unpleasant?

117
00:06:09,677 --> 00:06:11,278
Nothing like that.

118
00:06:11,378 --> 00:06:15,382
It's like this, just like that...
They all suddenly disappeared.

119
00:06:16,083 --> 00:06:17,184
Damn, it's messed up!

120
00:06:17,284 --> 00:06:20,988
You'll all be fine when you leave.
But what about me? Me!

121
00:06:39,206 --> 00:06:40,307
Mom.

122
00:06:40,307 --> 00:06:41,508
Coming only now?

123
00:06:41,508 --> 00:06:42,409
You were drinking?

124
00:06:42,409 --> 00:06:45,312
Yeah.. Dinner party.

125
00:06:45,312 --> 00:06:45,913
Why are you here?

126
00:06:46,013 --> 00:06:48,215
Came out to pee, but couldn't get back in.

127
00:06:48,415 --> 00:06:52,219
Damn, this place really sucks. To any restroom
in this residential area, it is 3 miles!

128
00:06:52,219 --> 00:06:54,321
Gosh, they should let us use
at least a potty, seriously!

129
00:06:54,421 --> 00:06:58,225
But street lights are bright, so I wasn't
scared at night. Now, that is great!

130
00:06:58,225 --> 00:07:02,229
Even if it's night, I need not come to get you.
That's all really great, yeah sure!

131
00:07:02,730 --> 00:07:07,134
If he's giving a remote, give it fast!
Why make us wait for a car to come?

132
00:07:07,635 --> 00:07:10,738
It's really petty, really.

133
00:07:16,543 --> 00:07:20,447
<i>Do the surgery on Monday.
Stay for 2 days afterwards.</i>

134
00:07:37,564 --> 00:07:39,166
Get up. The car's here.

135
00:07:54,381 --> 00:07:55,983
You've returned?

136
00:07:55,983 --> 00:07:58,886
Any inconvenience, yet?

137
00:07:59,787 --> 00:08:04,792
Well... When can we get the
shutter remote, I wonder...

138
00:08:04,792 --> 00:08:06,794
That's right. Here!

139
00:08:06,794 --> 00:08:07,995
Thank you.

140
00:08:12,299 --> 00:08:14,001
How come so...

141
00:08:15,302 --> 00:08:19,405
How come you look so distressed?

142
00:08:19,405 --> 00:08:22,809
Is it that obvious... on me?

143
00:08:24,311 --> 00:08:27,114
That is... sort of... like that.

144
00:08:27,114 --> 00:08:28,515
What is it?

145
00:08:28,716 --> 00:08:33,320
That day I happened to overhear.
It seemed you talked of cancer.

146
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:35,823
Are you seriously ill?

147
00:08:36,624 --> 00:08:38,826
Is it really showing?

148
00:08:41,528 --> 00:08:43,931
I must undergo surgery, in 3 days.

149
00:08:43,931 --> 00:08:45,833
Ah, I see...

150
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:47,935
That is a secret.

151
00:08:48,035 --> 00:08:51,238
Other than my wife, nobody knows it.

152
00:08:51,238 --> 00:08:57,645
If other family folks know,
it will throw them into chaos.

153
00:08:58,946 --> 00:09:01,448
Your dad is having a tumor surgery on Monday.

154
00:09:01,448 --> 00:09:02,349
What tumor?

155
00:09:02,349 --> 00:09:04,051
Something minuscule on the kidney.

156
00:09:04,151 --> 00:09:07,454
As I'm told, it's in fact a cancer.
As it's early, remove it and it's done.

157
00:09:07,454 --> 00:09:10,057
The surgery is simpler than
even an appendicitis surgery.

158
00:09:10,057 --> 00:09:11,759
No need to cut open anywhere else?

159
00:09:11,859 --> 00:09:13,761
Yes. Early stage.

160
00:09:13,761 --> 00:09:16,563
Saying the family would be in confusion
he had asked not to tell.

161
00:09:16,563 --> 00:09:18,065
But there was nothing here
to keep it a secret.

162
00:09:18,165 --> 00:09:19,867
So I am keeping you posted.

163
00:09:20,668 --> 00:09:22,069
Bo Yeong.

164
00:09:22,169 --> 00:09:25,172
Why keep it a secret? 
What big chaos?

165
00:09:25,172 --> 00:09:27,675
The fellow really goes overboard!

166
00:09:27,975 --> 00:09:32,580
Cheol Min. Why do you keep groaning
and squealing these days?

167
00:09:32,580 --> 00:09:34,582
Are you feeling unwell?

168
00:09:36,083 --> 00:09:37,284
You're back, dad?

169
00:09:37,885 --> 00:09:40,487
Dad, I heard you have a surgery on Monday?

170
00:09:41,388 --> 00:09:42,389
Who said that?

171
00:09:42,389 --> 00:09:43,290
Mom did.

172
00:09:43,390 --> 00:09:45,593
Have a great surgery. Fighting!

173
00:09:48,195 --> 00:09:53,100
Brat... Fine, this dad... will do the fighting.

174
00:09:53,100 --> 00:09:55,202
I wanted to keep it a secret
from you till the end...

175
00:09:55,202 --> 00:09:56,904
What's with you?

176
00:10:00,407 --> 00:10:01,809
Father.

177
00:10:01,909 --> 00:10:03,811
Please don't worry too much.

178
00:10:03,911 --> 00:10:07,615
Whatever happens, I won't cry.
So father, you too--

179
00:10:07,615 --> 00:10:09,316
Is he not going to croak it?

180
00:10:11,118 --> 00:10:12,820
Croak it...

181
00:10:20,928 --> 00:10:23,030
- Father.
- Cheol Min,

182
00:10:23,030 --> 00:10:24,632
What's wrong?

183
00:10:29,436 --> 00:10:31,038
I see. Good job.

184
00:10:31,739 --> 00:10:33,040
You're back?

185
00:10:33,540 --> 00:10:36,343
Why did you tell the family about the surgery?

186
00:10:36,944 --> 00:10:38,145
What's the big deal if I did?

187
00:10:38,245 --> 00:10:39,747
What? Somebody said something?

188
00:10:40,547 --> 00:10:42,349
Who cares to say anything?

189
00:10:42,750 --> 00:10:44,852
Who has any concern for me anyway?

190
00:10:44,952 --> 00:10:45,853
What is wrong?

191
00:10:45,953 --> 00:10:49,056
After talking of the surgery, there was
no big commotion, so you are angry?

192
00:10:49,356 --> 00:10:55,663
Su Yeong at least said a "fighting".
But my father... seriously!

193
00:11:46,814 --> 00:11:48,015
It's cold.

194
00:11:57,024 --> 00:11:58,826
So cold.

195
00:12:09,336 --> 00:12:11,639
I'm leaving to see Min Hyeok at the hospital.
You're going somewhere?

196
00:12:11,639 --> 00:12:13,340
I have to take this fellow to the vet.

197
00:12:13,340 --> 00:12:14,241
You want me to take you?

198
00:12:14,241 --> 00:12:17,044
It's fine. I'll walk over there.

199
00:12:27,054 --> 00:12:28,455
Hello--

200
00:12:31,859 --> 00:12:34,161
Her manners!

201
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:38,465
Where did the wretched girl go?

202
00:12:55,482 --> 00:12:58,085
Mom. I'm scared.

203
00:12:58,786 --> 00:13:01,488
The surgery is day after tomorrow.

204
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:05,893
I'm worried to death, about the fellow.

205
00:13:06,794 --> 00:13:09,196
All the odd thoughts come up suddenly.

206
00:13:09,196 --> 00:13:13,300
If it goes wrong and something happens
to the fellow, what will I do, I wonder.

207
00:13:13,901 --> 00:13:16,003
I keep tearing up...

208
00:13:16,103 --> 00:13:17,504
<i>Father.</i>

209
00:13:17,504 --> 00:13:19,807
I don't know if he can withstand a surgery.

210
00:13:19,807 --> 00:13:21,508
The fellow has some age too...

211
00:13:21,508 --> 00:13:23,811
<i>Please don't worry, father.</i>

212
00:13:23,811 --> 00:13:26,213
<i>I... shall firmly withstand it.</i>

213
00:13:26,213 --> 00:13:27,615
Please don't say such things.

214
00:13:27,715 --> 00:13:31,719
I can't live without the fellow.
I can't live even for a day.

215
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:37,024
Every day, he's so happy when I come in,
moving my heart.

216
00:13:37,925 --> 00:13:42,229
In the morning when my eyes are closed,
he comes to lick my face.

217
00:13:42,229 --> 00:13:45,232
Really... I can't live without this fellow.

218
00:13:45,232 --> 00:13:46,333
Bye then.

219
00:13:46,333 --> 00:13:47,134
Father!

220
00:13:47,134 --> 00:13:48,035
Oh so suddenly!

221
00:13:48,035 --> 00:13:49,336
Why do you yell and get on my nerves?

222
00:13:49,336 --> 00:13:50,838
So the fellow was Cheol Min?

223
00:13:50,838 --> 00:13:53,841
Without whom you won't live.
Thinking of whom brings out tears.

224
00:13:53,941 --> 00:13:57,244
The one who won't withstand
a surgery... is not me then!

225
00:13:57,244 --> 00:13:58,445
I am your son.

226
00:13:58,445 --> 00:13:59,546
I am cancer-stricken..

227
00:13:59,546 --> 00:14:02,750
What's with you? Your surgery is simple.
It's the early stages.

228
00:14:02,850 --> 00:14:05,953
But I have cancer you know!
Cancer, cancer. Cancer!

229
00:14:06,153 --> 00:14:07,855
What surgery does this whelp have?

230
00:14:07,955 --> 00:14:09,056
Does this whelp have cancer?

231
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:10,457
He has kidney trouble. Why?

232
00:14:10,457 --> 00:14:13,260
The whelp has some kidney stone.
I have cancer!

233
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:15,262
I'm your cancer-stricken son, okay!

234
00:14:15,262 --> 00:14:19,366
This whelp is not a person, but a dog!
All he has is kidney stones.

235
00:14:19,366 --> 00:14:22,269
I can't even get as much of your
concern as this whelp does? Huh?

236
00:14:22,369 --> 00:14:27,174
- You stupid fellow!
- Father, you never liked me even
getting into your sight, no? Right?

237
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:31,779
The moment you gave a son of a bitch
a human name, I knew it!

238
00:14:31,879 --> 00:14:34,782
This whelp is more of a son to you than me?
Right?

239
00:14:34,782 --> 00:14:35,583
Dad, why are you like this?

240
00:14:35,683 --> 00:14:37,184
Let go! 
Father!

241
00:14:37,184 --> 00:14:40,087
You really shouldn't be treating me like this!

242
00:14:40,387 --> 00:14:45,292
Once I'm dead and gone, you can be
with this whelp for a million years...

243
00:14:46,193 --> 00:14:47,394
Dad.

