00:28:53,140 --> 00:28:56,143
When I got your call earlier, I was a little lost.

488
00:28:56,343 --> 00:28:58,045
But now I feel right about this.

489
00:28:59,647 --> 00:29:03,250
As I met you so suddenly last time,
there was a lot that I couldn't say.

490
00:29:03,350 --> 00:29:05,152
What is it that you couldn't say?

491
00:29:05,152 --> 00:29:09,056
First of all, so happy to see you.
Really!

492
00:29:09,056 --> 00:29:13,160
And then, have you been doing well?

493
00:29:18,065 --> 00:29:23,570
It is like I had a lot to say.
But I don't remember anything.

494
00:29:24,772 --> 00:29:26,774
So I get scared.

495
00:29:26,874 --> 00:29:29,677
As I don't know what I might have lost.

496
00:29:30,277 --> 00:29:33,080
Thoughts will slowly come out.
Please don't get too worried.

497
00:29:33,180 --> 00:29:37,184
Everybody at the company is looking forward
to you getting healthy and returning, CEO sir.

498
00:29:37,284 --> 00:29:40,187
Because in our company, you are...
like this!

499
00:29:41,589 --> 00:29:45,092
I... What kind of person was I?

500
00:29:45,292 --> 00:29:47,795
What kind of person you were, you mean?

501
00:29:49,697 --> 00:29:53,200
Can I tell you as we eat the ice cream?
I think it should be frozen by now.

502
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:54,602
Fine.

503
00:29:55,302 --> 00:30:00,107
Last time when you asked me to get it, a child had
bought ice cream and was eating something else.

504
00:30:00,107 --> 00:30:02,409
It is that ice cream that 
you want to eat first, right?

505
00:30:05,012 --> 00:30:06,413
Are you sleepy?

506
00:30:06,413 --> 00:30:07,514
No, I'm not.

507
00:30:07,615 --> 00:30:09,617
If you are sleepy, you want to
sleep and eat it later?

508
00:30:09,617 --> 00:30:11,418
If you eat it now, you will 
have to brush your teeth.

509
00:30:11,518 --> 00:30:14,321
It's all right. Please tell me the things.

510
00:30:14,622 --> 00:30:19,627
Sure. First, you are a smart person
who is even a Harvard graduate.

511
00:30:19,627 --> 00:30:21,528
What is this harvard?

512
00:30:22,329 --> 00:30:25,132
It is the best university in the world.

513
00:30:25,232 --> 00:30:27,735
Even with that, you were quite humble.

514
00:30:27,735 --> 00:30:30,537
<i>There are two ways to be successful in life.</i>

515
00:30:30,638 --> 00:30:33,841
<i>Either you're great,
or you stick alongside someone great.</i>

516
00:30:33,841 --> 00:30:36,844
<i>If I am of the first type,
you are all of the second type.</i>

517
00:30:37,444 --> 00:30:38,946
<i>Because you met me.</i>

518
00:30:39,046 --> 00:30:42,249
You were always warm and friendly with people.

519
00:30:42,249 --> 00:30:46,553
<i>Hating those gasbags who tout their worthless
degrees, I had picked you instead, Na Jin A.</i>

520
00:30:46,954 --> 00:30:49,156
<i>But it's equally useless after all.</i>

521
00:30:49,456 --> 00:30:55,462
More than anything, you're the one who let me
join the company... which I'm thankful for.

522
00:31:08,475 --> 00:31:09,777
Ice Cream...

523
00:31:09,977 --> 00:31:11,078
It is right here.

524
00:31:11,078 --> 00:31:12,980
Sleep and eat it later.

525
00:31:13,681 --> 00:31:15,983
Put it in the fridge.

526
00:31:15,983 --> 00:31:18,786
Yes. I'll put in the fridge.

527
00:31:18,786 --> 00:31:20,688
Ms. Na Jin A.

528
00:31:20,688 --> 00:31:22,089
Yes?

529
00:31:23,090 --> 00:31:32,000
- Later on... Is it okay to call you again?
- Yes.

530
00:32:20,848 --> 00:32:22,149
